==English==

===Etymology===
Greek; loving + man: French ''philanthrope''.

===Noun===
'''philanthropist'''
#A person who loves mankind (the human race) in general.
#A [[very]] generous person or institution.

====Translations====
'''person who loves mankind'''
*French: [[philanthrope]]
'''very generous person'''
*French: [[philanthrope]]

